  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Priyansh, the way you described teamwork in your project had such clear weight — what part of that moment still stands out for you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The moment when we fixed the bug right before the deadline. Everyone worked together, like magic. It felt so satisfying. Do you ever get that in your work?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — that kind of last-minute magic is its own reward. What made the teamwork click so well?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe because we all had different skills but trusted each other. No ego, just focus. One person was *shrewd* with debugging, another good at planning. You know, like a cricket team? Everyone has their role."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Exactly — and just like a cricket team, no one shines alone. What role do you usually play in these moments?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly the planner or the support player. I make sure things don’t fall apart while others do the sharp work. Like a *wicketkeeper* in cricket — not the star, but important. What about you? Do you like working in teams?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Good comparison — a wicketkeeper is the quiet hero. I love how teams flow when everyone knows their part. What’s your go-to snack when you’re in focus mode?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, usually something crunchy. Like *chips* or roasted chana. Keeps me going during long coding sessions. You? Do you eat while working or prefer a clean desk?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Crunchy and focused — I get that. I sip tea, but respect the clean desk vibe. What’s your favorite tea pairing — milk or plain?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Milk tea with a lot of sugar — I know, not healthy, but it’s my *chai* comfort. Sometimes I add a biscuit. You? What’s your style?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Milk and sugar — pure joy on a workday. I stick to plain, but I admire the boldness. Do you ever switch to something lighter on weekends?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "On weekends, I switch to green tea or sometimes just water with lemon. It feels refreshing, and I can think better. Also, I watch some Bollywood movies — they’re a nice break. Have you seen any lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Green tea and Bollywood — a calm, smart combo. I get that balance. What movie caught your eye this time?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I watched *Pathaan* recently — it’s a big hit here! The action scenes are crazy, but Imaad Shah’s comedy parts made me laugh a lot. You know Bollywood movies, right? Or maybe you prefer something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Pathaan was a blast — action and comedy in perfect mix. Imaad’s timing is magic. Do you watch many action movies, or pick ones with a good story?\""
    }
  ],
